# VibrationFit Project Rules

## 🔒 FEATURE REGISTRY (READ THIS FIRST!)

**CRITICAL:** Before modifying ANY feature, check `FEATURE_REGISTRY.md` in the project root.

| Status | Your Action |
|--------|-------------|
| 🔒 **LOCKED** | **DO NOT MODIFY** without explicit user permission. Feature is working in production. |
| ✅ **STABLE** | Modify with extreme caution. Test thoroughly after any changes. |
| 🚧 **IN PROGRESS** | Safe to modify. |
| ⚠️ **NEEDS REVIEW** | Verify it works before relying on it. |

**Before touching Life Vision, Token System, Design System, or Database Schema:**
1. Read `FEATURE_REGISTRY.md` 
2. Check feature status
3. If 🔒 LOCKED, ask user for permission
4. Document current behavior
5. Create test plan
6. Make changes incrementally
7. Test ENTIRE feature (not just your change)
8. Update version in registry

---

## 📁 File Organization (CRITICAL - READ FIRST)

### Documentation Files
**NEVER create documentation files in project root!** Always use the appropriate folder:

| File Type | Location | Examples |
|-----------|----------|----------|
| **Database docs** | `supabase/` | Schema dumps, migration guides |
| **Feature docs** | `docs/` | Implementation guides, expert guides |
| **API docs** | `docs/api/` | API endpoint documentation |
| **Design docs** | `docs/design/` | Design system, brand guidelines |
| **Deployment docs** | `docs/deployment/` | Deployment checklists, strategies |
| **Architecture docs** | `docs/architecture/` | System architecture, data flow |
| **Project planning** | `docs/planning/` | Feature plans, roadmaps |

### Database Files
**ALL database-related files go in `supabase/`:**

```
supabase/
├── COMPLETE_SCHEMA_DUMP.sql    ← Production schema dump (source of truth)
├── CURRENT_SCHEMA.md           ← Human-readable schema docs
├── MIGRATION_STRATEGY.md       ← Migration workflow guide
├── migrations/                 ← Active migration files
│   └── YYYYMMDDHHMMSS_description.sql
└── archive/                    ← Archived/old files
```

**Reference for schema questions:**
- ✅ `supabase/CURRENT_SCHEMA.md` (human-readable)
- ✅ `supabase/COMPLETE_SCHEMA_DUMP.sql` (exact definitions)
- ❌ DO NOT reference files in `supabase/archive/` (outdated)

### Source Code Files
**Application code structure:**

```
src/
├── app/                        ← Next.js pages & API routes
│   ├── api/                    ← API endpoints
│   ├── (auth)/                 ← Auth-related pages
│   ├── dashboard/              ← Dashboard pages
│   └── life-vision/            ← Life vision features
├── components/                 ← React components
├── lib/                        ← Utility libraries
│   ├── design-system/          ← Design system components
│   ├── viva/                   ← VIVA AI system
│   │   ├── prompts/            ← Centralized AI prompts
│   │   └── ...
│   ├── supabase/               ← Supabase client utilities
│   └── ...
└── hooks/                      ← React hooks
```

### Rules for Creating New Files

**Documentation:**
1. ❌ NEVER create `.md` files in project root
2. ✅ ALWAYS place in appropriate `docs/` subfolder
3. ✅ Update `docs/README.md` if creating new category
4. ✅ ALWAYS add date header to guide docs (Last Updated: Month Day, Year)

**Migrations:**
1. ❌ NEVER create migration files outside `supabase/migrations/`
2. ✅ Use timestamp format: `YYYYMMDDHHMMSS_description.sql`
3. ✅ Create the migration file, then STOP - user will run it manually
4. ⚠️ NEVER update `supabase/COMPLETE_SCHEMA_DUMP.sql` or `supabase/CURRENT_SCHEMA.md` automatically
5. ℹ️ User will update schema docs after manually running the migration

**AI Prompts:**
1. ❌ NEVER embed prompts directly in API routes
2. ✅ Centralize in `src/lib/viva/prompts/`
3. ✅ Export through `src/lib/viva/prompts/index.ts`

**Temporary/Debug Files:**
1. ❌ NEVER commit debug files to root
2. ✅ Use `temp/` folder (gitignored)
3. ✅ One-off scripts go in `scripts/[category]/`
4. ✅ Clean up after debugging

**Utility Scripts:**
1. ✅ Place in `scripts/database/`, `scripts/lambda/`, `scripts/video/`, etc.
2. ✅ After running successfully, move to `scripts/archive/`
3. ❌ NEVER commit large zip files (add to .gitignore)

**AWS Deployment:**
1. ❌ NEVER commit Lambda layers to git (use AWS deployment)
2. ❌ NEVER commit Lambda functions (functions/) - deploy to AWS
3. ❌ NEVER commit production data dumps (production-*.json)
4. ✅ Place AWS configs in `scripts/aws/`
5. ✅ Keep AWS scripts for deployment automation

### Before Creating Any File, Ask:
1. **Is this documentation?** → `docs/[category]/`
2. **Is this database-related?** → `supabase/`
3. **Is this a component?** → `src/components/`
4. **Is this a utility?** → `src/lib/`
5. **Is this a page?** → `src/app/`
6. **Is this an API?** → `src/app/api/`

### File Naming Conventions
- **Components:** PascalCase (`UserProfile.tsx`)
- **Utilities:** kebab-case (`text-metrics.ts`)
- **API routes:** kebab-case (`route.ts` in folder)
- **Docs:** SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE or kebab-case (`MIGRATION_STRATEGY.md`)
- **Migrations:** `YYYYMMDDHHMMSS_description.sql`

