## 🎬 Video Asset URL Rules (CRITICAL)

### MediaConvert Thumbnail Pattern

When uploading a video to S3, the MediaConvert Lambda function automatically generates output files following this naming convention:

| Output | Suffix | Example |
|--------|--------|---------|
| **1080p video** | `-1080p.mp4` | `offer-video-3-6-26-1080p.mp4` |
| **720p video** | `-720p.mp4` | `offer-video-3-6-26-720p.mp4` |
| **Original video** | `-original.mp4` | `offer-video-3-6-26-original.mp4` |
| **Thumbnail** | `-thumb.0000000.jpg` | `offer-video-3-6-26-thumb.0000000.jpg` |

**To get a thumbnail URL from a video URL, replace the quality suffix:**
- `{base}-1080p.mp4` → `{base}-thumb.0000000.jpg`
- `{base}-720p.mp4` → `{base}-thumb.0000000.jpg`

**CDN base URLs:**
- ✅ `https://media.vibrationfit.com/site-assets/video/...` (CDN - preferred)
- ✅ `https://vibration-fit-client-storage.s3.amazonaws.com/site-assets/video/...` (S3 direct)

### Auto-Derived Thumbnails in Video Component

The `<Video>` component from the design system **automatically derives** the thumbnail from the `src` URL when no `poster` prop is provided. You do NOT need to manually specify a poster for MediaConvert-processed videos.

```tsx
// Thumbnail auto-derived as offer-video-3-6-26-thumb.0000000.jpg
<Video src="https://media.vibrationfit.com/site-assets/video/marketing/offer/offer-video-3-6-26-1080p.mp4" />

// Override with explicit poster only when needed
<Video src="..." poster="https://media.vibrationfit.com/custom-poster.jpg" />
```

**Utility function:** `getVideoThumbnailUrl(videoUrl)` is exported from `@/lib/design-system/components` for use outside the Video component.

**❌ NEVER guess thumbnail patterns like `-poster.jpg` or `-thumbnail.jpg`**
**✅ ALWAYS use the `-thumb.0000000.jpg` suffix or let the Video component auto-derive it**

